<Stem>
	<Paragraph><Sentence>Give the first 4 terms of a sequence that 
                             satisfies the following:</Sentence> 
        </Paragraph>
        <Blockquote>
	  <Paragraph><Sentence>1. The first two terms are each negative integers 
                                  between -3 and -1, inclusive.</Sentence> 
          </Paragraph>
	  <Paragraph><Sentence>2. Each subsequent term is a sum of the previous
                                  two terms.</Sentence> 
          </Paragraph>
        </Blockquote>
        <Paragraph><Sentence>
          <Emphasis>Note:</Emphasis> There is more than one correct answer. Any example 
           you choose that meets the above requirements will be scored as correct.   
        </Sentence></Paragraph>
</Stem>
